<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Revocation of Foreign Trawlers' Licenses Urged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2301143894 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2301143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The operating licence of foreign fishing boats in 
Aceh waters should be revoked because they often violate 
existing regulations, including the clause banning them from 
operating within 12 miles from the coast. Colonel Rudi 
Supriatna, commander of 012 Military Area Command, said Thai 
trawlers flying Indonesian flags, who operate in the western 
Aceh waters, often violate this clause. 
  The commander, who was aboard the Indonesian Navy's Nomad 
plane along with Navy Commodore Widodo, commander of the Western 
Fleet's Naval Combat Group, made an inspection tour of western 
Aceh waters today. During the inspection tour, they found three 
foreign fishing boats in (Calang) waters, western Aceh, at about 
156 km west of Banda Aceh and they were operating within 12 
miles from the coast. Another violation committed by the 
trawlers was the use of drift nets, which are capable of 
catching all types of fish. 

</TEXT>

