<H3> <TI>   `First Batch' of Refugees From Japan Arrives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2501063594 Hanoi VNA in English 0621 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2501063594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan. 25 -- Two hundred and three 
Vietnamese nationals returning from a refugee camp in Japan 
arrived in Hai Phong yesterday. 
  They belong to the first batch of 263 returnees from Japan. 
Most of them are young people from Kien Thuy, Do Son town and 
Le Chan precinct of Hai Phong Port City. These returnees are not 
beneficiaries from the fund provided by the United Nations High 
Commissioner for Refugees because they illegally left the 
country after Sept. 27, 1991. 

