<F P=102>  BK2601155894 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2601155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The newspaper CAMBODIA LIFE on 19 January quoted 
sources as saying that a Khmer Rouge [KR] general named Chhit 
Choeun or Mok, now on convalescence in the triborder area of 
Cambodia, Laos, and Thailand has ordered Khmer Rouge's 980th [as 
heard] Division headed by (Muol) to resume its intensified 
operations around the Tonle Sap lake area to kill fishermen of 
Vietnamese origin who are earning their living by fishing in the 
Tonle Sap lake. 

</TEXT>

