<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two More Domestic Airlines To Open Mid-Apr </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2301092294 Hanoi VNA in English 0537 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2301092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan. 23 -- Two more domestic airways, 
Hanoi-Dien Bien (Lai Chau Province) and Hanoi-Na San (Son La 
Province), will be reopened by mid-April this year. 
  More than 1 billion dong (roughly USD 100,000) have been 
spent in rebuilding the Dien Bien Airport, supplying it with air 
traffic control equipment, and building an air services system. 
  To upgrade the Na San Airport will take about 250 million 
dong (roughly USD 25,000). And to keep regular arrivals at the 
airport will need a further 1.2 billion dong (approximately USD 
120,000). 
  Operators will be Vietnam Airlines, Pacific Airlines and 
Vasco. 
  These two airports fell into disuse three to four years ago 
due to the lack of passengers and poor infrastructure. 
  Now growing demand for fast transport to serve tourism and 
business has prompted the Vietnam General Department of Civil 
Aviation to reopen these short flights between northern airports. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

