<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nong Duc Manh Receives Bac Son Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2501103594 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2501103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the afternoon of 22 January, Comrade Nong Duc 
Manh, member of the Political Bureau and chairman of the 
National Assembly, received at the National Assembly Building a 
delegation of cadres in charge of village and city grass-roots 
establishments in Bac Son District, Lang Son Province. 
  Chairman Nong Duc Manh was briefed by the comrade head 
delegate on the socioeconomic situations in all villages in the 
district. Next, two delegates -- one from the village that 
scores the best achievements and the other from the village that 
faces the most difficult problems -- briefed him on the living 
conditions, economic growth, and party-building work at the 
grass-roots establishments under their charge. 
  Chairman Nong Duc Manh was very happy to learn about those 
changes for the better. He warmly commended grass-roots party 
organizations and administrative organs in Bac Son District for 
having upheld the traditions of a revolutionary base and scored 
encouraging economic achievements. The planting of fruit trees 
and industrial crops has helped with the production of commodity 
goods. Small-scale hydroelectric power plants are working fairly 
well. All those achievements have contributed to improving the 
living conditions of ethnic minority compatriots to an important 
degree. 
  Chairman Nong Duc Manh expressed his hope that grass-roots 
party committee echelons and administrative organs in Bac Son 
District would continue to develop their revolutionary 
traditions and direct the people in satisfactorily carrying out 
the renovation cause and in materializing the goals of making 
the people rich and the country powerful and of bringinging 
about justice and civilization in society. 

</TEXT>

