Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Defense Ministry, in connection with rumors 
regarding the deployment of Patriot antimissile batteries, said 
"it seems that the U.S. Army is positively reviewing plans to 
ship defensive antimissile batteries to the ROK as part of the 
plan for U.S. Forces in the ROK." 
  The Defense Ministry, however, said that "there has been no 
discussion or agreement yet on the timing and scale of the 
deployment of Patriot antimissile batteries," and added that 
"the ROK and the United States will, in the future, closely 
confer on the issue." 

