<H3> <TI>   Mozambique Prepares for Kim Chong-il's Birthday </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2801114694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1018 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2801114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 28 (KCNA) -- An inaugural 
ceremony of the preparatory committee for celebrating the 
birthday of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il was held in 
Maputo of Mozambique on January 20. 
  The meeting elected the minister of interior of Mozambique 
chairman of the preparatory committee and decided to set 20 days 
from February 1 as a period of celebration functions. 
  In his speech, the chairman of the preparatory committee 
said 
that on this occasion celebration meetings, film shows, photo 
exhibitions and other functions would be held in cities and 
rural villages, industrial establishments and organs of 
Mozambique. 

