<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC To Post Military Attache at ROK Embassy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2801015494 Seoul YONHAP in English 0105 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2801015494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Jan. 28 (YONHAP) -- Beijing will post a 
military attache to its embassy in Seoul next month, a Foreign 
Ministry official said Friday. The Chinese Government recently 
called on the South Korean Government to allow a Chinese 
military attache to work at the Chinese Embassy here, he said. 
  "We finished considering whether to accept the colonel-grade 
Chinese military attache and found no problem, so he will be 
able to posted here in February." Seoul's military attache 
began his service in Beijing on Dec. 25 last year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-48731 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas019_d_94007" </HT>


