<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karen Rebels Destroy Water Pumps in Thaton </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2801013794 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 27 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2801013794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Concerted efforts are being made to produce 800 
million baskets of paddy annually to realize the major objective 
of the state government in developing the national economy. 
Double cropping and cultivation of summer paddy are being 
carried out to achieve this objective. 
  Ten members of the Karen armed organization in the jungle, 
who do not wish to see the economic progress of the nation and 
the farmers, mined and destroyed three Chinese-made Dinzin Brand 
400 horsepower water pumps being used for cultivation of summer 
paddy in Mogaung village tract, Thaton Township, after midnight 
on 24 January. Our military columns are pursuing the members of 
the armed Karen organization who mined and destroyed the water 
pumps. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

