<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report on P3C Construction Site Change Denied </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1601065494 Naha OKINAWA TIMES in Japanese 15 Jan 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1601065494 </F>
<F P=104>  Naha OKINAWA TIMES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo -- At a regular news conference on 14 January 
Akira Takeshita, deputy director-general of the Defense 
Facilities Administration Agency [DFAA], commented on a report 
that the Maritime Self Defense Force's [MSDF] Staff Office is 
considering changing the construction site of a P3C transmitting 
station on Okinawa from Toyohara District in Motobu-cho to Ie 
Island in the face of strong protests from Motobu residents. 
Takeshita said: "The agency in charge of the construction has 
not been informed of any change." He also denied the report, 
saying his inquiry with the Maritime Staff Office has confirmed 
"such is not the case." 
  Meanwhile, it is also true that the DFAA has not much time 
left to execute the budget for the construction of the P3C 
communications facility. Furthermore, since the government 
formulation of the fiscal 1994 budget has been delayed this 
year, and the work on formulating the portion of the budget 
concerning the P3C project will begin in about a month, no doubt 
the DFAA faces a major problem in regards to the construction 
project which is making no headway. 

</TEXT>

