<H3> <TI>   Border Agreement Signed With Russia, PRC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2701201994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1925 GMT 27 Jan 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2701201994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 27 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Today at 
the Ministry for External Relations of Mongolia signed was the 
inter-government agreement on definition of the junction points 
of the borders of Mongolia, the Russian Federation and the 
People's Republic of China by the First Vice-Minister of 
External Relations of Mongolia J. Choinhor [name as received], 
the Ambassador of Russia to Mongolia S.S. Razov, the Ambassador 
of China to Mongolia Pei Jiayi. 
  J. Choinhor characterized the signing of the 
inter-government 
agreement as a manifestation of the respect for sovereignty of 
Mongolia on the part of China and Russia. 
  Tne Russian Ambassador S.S. Razov highly valued the work of 
the experts of the three sides and noted that the signing of the 
inter-government agreement is not just an event of a technical 
character, but is of great importance [for] relations, not only 
in trilateral but in development of constructive, positive 
changes in mutual relations in this region. 
  The Ambassador of China to Mongolia Pei Jiayi noted that the 
signing of the agreement is a contribution to the development of 
friendly relations and cooperation between the countries and a 
guarantee for stability on borders of Mongolia, China, Russia. 

</TEXT>

