<H3> <TI>   Nation's Leading Foreign Trade Partners Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2101184194 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1737 GMT 21 Jan 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2101184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 21 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- At 
present Mongolia maintains trade relationships with some 47 
world's countries. The country's leading trading partner 
remains Russia on share of which falls some 48 per cent of the 
total foreign trade turnover of Mongolia. 
  After Russia there are the People's Republic of China 24 per 
cent, Kazahstan 7.5 per cent Japan 4.9 and the USA 2.9 per cent 
respectively. In 1993 year Mongolia realized foreign trade 
turnover of 722 million USD [U.S. dollars] worth, 160.9 million 
out of which constitute export and some 161.5 million import. 
[figures as received] Over 37 per cent of foreign trade for 
the last year account for the private sector's enterprises. 
This implies that their share in the foreign trade contacts of 
the country has been doubled in comparison with that for the 
year of 1992. 

</TEXT>

