<H3> <TI>   MONTSAME Reviews Press for 25 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2601004894 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 2243 GMT 25 Jan 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2601004894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 25 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
outcome of checking the activities of the general board on 
ensuring the state security and the central police department by 
the working group of the parliament. The representatives of the 
opposition group in the parliament noted that the chairman and 
deputy chairman and the prime minister as well have expressed 
their request to check the above mentioned accusations of their 
so called abusing the official powers. They refused to give any 
commentaries on this point pleading the necessity to adhere to 
the parliamentary ethics. The capital city newspaper 
"ULAANBAATAR" published an article by scholar S. Ichinnorov on 
the creation of the present Mongolian capital. The article says 
that the city was founded as far back as 1639 and had been 
transferred from time to time until its stationing on its 
present site. Those movings of the capital historian is 
explaining in connection with the traditions of the people and 
necessity of nature protection. 
  Besides this he considers that among the other reasons there 
were aggressions of the neighbouring western tribes and the 
needs for maintaining commercial and economic relations. 
  Journalist O. Lhagvadorj in his article in the newspaper 
doubts whether the granting of the building of a club having 
been named after Lenin on lease to Russian citizen S. P. Kokarev 
was legitimate. The above mentioned citizen in his turn began 
letting lease of the building to various organizations which was 
recognized by the chief of the Consular Department of the 
Russian Embassy to Mongolia as being a violation of the decree 
of the Mongolian Government, the newspaper informs. 

</TEXT>

